17
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:25,830
Our valley is a place of legacy.

18
00:01:26,331 --> 00:01:28,813
Monuments of wood and bronze and stone.

19
00:01:28,914 --> 00:01:31,276
Stories we tell and make our own.

20
00:01:31,837 --> 00:01:34,379
Colonial towns that stand the test of time.

21
00:01:34,559 --> 00:01:37,783
Old graveyards that reckon our lost prime.

22
00:01:38,083 --> 00:01:40,686
Thoughts that bring a poet to a rhyme.

23
00:01:41,186 --> 00:01:42,608
And a river runs through it.

24
00:01:43,598 --> 00:02:01,193
Our valley is a place of history, heroes that fought in foreign wars, Army, Navy, Air Force, and the Corps, pride and service that extends their tours, courage seeping, sweating through their pores, death and loss that bravery ignores, and a river runs through it.

25
00:02:02,788 --> 00:02:05,430
Our valley is a place of misery.

26
00:02:06,091 --> 00:02:08,773
Native kindness lost in exploitation.

27
00:02:09,374 --> 00:02:12,597
Liberties for some through subjugation.

28
00:02:13,117 --> 00:02:15,539
Faith distortions used to build a nation.

29
00:02:15,639 --> 00:02:17,901
Confinement to the distant reservation.

30
00:02:18,261 --> 00:02:20,704
Hopeful spirits lost at every station.

31
00:02:20,764 --> 00:02:23,886
Museum cases filled with infiltration.

32
00:02:24,607 --> 00:02:25,748
And a river runs through it.

33
00:02:26,845 --> 00:02:43,753
Our valley is a place of shame, treaties that were violated, tribes that were decimated, disease that was initiated, environment that was devastated, trust that was annihilated, greed that is still celebrated, and a river runs through it.

34
00:02:45,014 --> 00:02:47,135
Our valley is a place of industry.

35
00:02:47,495 --> 00:02:51,417
Iron was smelted, tallow was melted, ships were built, frames were gilt.

36
00:02:53,123 --> 00:02:54,144
Leather was tanned.

37
00:02:54,204 --> 00:02:55,305
Bridges were spanned.

38
00:02:55,386 --> 00:02:56,407
Fabric was dyed.

39
00:02:56,527 --> 00:02:57,448
Fish was fried.

40
00:02:57,528 --> 00:02:58,589
Rum was distilled.

41
00:02:58,669 --> 00:02:59,790
Barrels were filled.

42
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:00,871
Glass was blown.

43
00:03:00,992 --> 00:03:01,933
Crops were grown.

44
00:03:02,273 --> 00:03:03,394
Meadows were stamped.

45
00:03:03,494 --> 00:03:04,515
Soldiers encamped.

46
00:03:04,656 --> 00:03:08,720
Milk was homogenized, pasteurized, and fortified.

47
00:03:09,220 --> 00:03:10,442
And a river runs through it.

48
00:03:11,544 --> 00:03:13,326
Our valley is a place of industry.

49
00:03:13,406 --> 00:03:15,409
Lies were told as papers passed.

50
00:03:15,469 --> 00:03:17,711
Covenants never intended to last.

51
00:03:17,751 --> 00:03:19,854
Stolen lands, great wealth amassed.

52
00:03:20,134 --> 00:03:22,377
Rampant corruption now put on blast.

53
00:03:22,597 --> 00:03:24,599
How did it get so bad so fast?

54
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:27,202
This silent guilt that sanitizes.

55
00:03:27,342 --> 00:03:29,265
Race unrest that paralyzes.

56
00:03:29,685 --> 00:03:31,266
Black lives trying to matter.

57
00:03:31,346 --> 00:03:32,948
Brown skin made to scatter.

58
00:03:33,008 --> 00:03:34,529
Red blood spilt and splattered.

59
00:03:34,849 --> 00:03:36,551
Homes that only sell to some.

60
00:03:36,971 --> 00:03:38,592
Banks don't lend to everyone.

61
00:03:38,712 --> 00:03:40,894
Police don't look to serve and protect.

62
00:03:41,274 --> 00:03:45,738
Fear and loathing breed disrespect and a river runs through it.

63
00:03:46,920 --> 00:04:12,832
Our valley is still a place of denial, for graves undug to drive a pile, for landed gentry remains on trial, for sins committed in the church's aisle and failure to turn equality's dial, for actions thought both vain and vile, no small amount of desecration where progress interred the bones of First Nation, with never a notion to a real preservation and a headlong rush toward contamination.

64
00:04:13,512 --> 00:04:15,637
Where is Missituck's compensation?

65
00:04:16,077 --> 00:04:18,663
Are bluebacks and herring a standing ovation?

66
00:04:19,184 --> 00:04:23,492
The watchers gather around the formation and a river runs through it.

67
00:04:24,785 --> 00:04:34,433
Our valley is a place of nativity, indigenous braves or slaves in captivity, immigrant enclaves in exclusivity, a treacherous path to beloved community.

68
00:04:34,793 --> 00:04:50,325
Each clan wears a kindred face, covets a homeland's warm embrace, coveting gospels of time and space, every religion and every race, tribal spirits of fire and ice, a thousand types of beans and rice, and a river runs through it.

69
00:04:51,515 --> 00:04:55,618
Our valley is a place of fertility, verdant shores by the sandy beaches.

70
00:04:56,078 --> 00:05:07,866
Nature grows what the soul beseeches, ash and elm and maple preaches from the silent spring to the epic speeches, yet poisoned into the soil leeches, open wounds and ugly breaches.

71
00:05:08,146 --> 00:05:12,429
We've yet to learn what nature teaches and a river runs through it.

72
00:05:13,756 --> 00:05:15,436
Our valley is a tapestry.

73
00:05:15,957 --> 00:05:17,977
Threads for every color and shade.

74
00:05:18,057 --> 00:05:20,098
Stripes for every soul displayed.

75
00:05:20,538 --> 00:05:21,498
Winter and spring.

76
00:05:21,618 --> 00:05:22,678
Summer and fall.

77
00:05:22,758 --> 00:05:26,059
Translucent rain that showers all.

78
00:05:26,479 --> 00:05:28,680
Rainbows await the heart's desire.

79
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:31,280
Together we face the cleansing fire.

80
00:05:31,821 --> 00:05:34,321
Families grow strong with true resilience.

81
00:05:34,401 --> 00:05:37,602
Schools invest in each child's brilliance.

82
00:05:38,202 --> 00:05:40,823
Each one brings their gifts and talents.

83
00:05:41,790 --> 00:05:44,633
God's design puts the scales in balance.

84
00:05:44,713 --> 00:05:49,539
